[Student "S"]
{[show S]
[BID 2!H] [BID 3NT]
[show NS]
The chances of a slam on this hand are very small, and if NORTH decides to use RKCB it will 
just confuse matters when SOUTH shows two Key Cards.
 

 
NORTH has a better way to find out about the hand. She bids 2NT asking SOUTH to further describe 
his hand. SOUTH should then bid 3NT, showing a solid suit headed by AKQ.
 

 
SOUTH cannot have as much as an extra Jack, so NORTH just passes 3NT.}


